HEADWORD: Invertebrate
<hw>In*ver"te*brate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Destitute of a backbone; having no vertebr⟦ae⟧; of or pertaining to
the Invertebrata.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the
Invertebrata.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Age of invertebrates</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Age</er>, and
